hydra-llm (0.1.12-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New `hydra-llm config <alias>` subcommand: read or write per-alias
    overrides for server-launch settings. Writes go to a JSON file
    under ~/.config/hydra-llm/server/<alias>.json so they survive
    catalog updates and don't pollute the main config.yaml.
  * Layered resolution at start time: llama-server defaults -> catalog
    entry -> global config.yaml -> per-alias override (narrowest
    wins). Provenance is shown in `hydra-llm config <alias>` output
    so it's obvious which layer set each value.
  * Settings supported in this release:
      reasoning_format       none | deepseek | hide | off
      predict                uncapped | off | <int>
      extra_args             list of additional llama-server flags
      chat_template_kwargs   JSON dict (enables disabling thinking
                             mode on gemma-4 et al via
                             {"enable_thinking": false})
  * Live apply: when an alias is currently running, `hydra-llm config`
    detects whether the change requires a server restart and prompts
    before doing it. Pass --restart to skip the prompt, --no-restart
    to apply on next start instead.
  * docker_driver now consumes the resolved settings dict instead of
    reading individual keys directly from the global config; same
    behaviour for users who never set a per-alias override.
  * `hydra-llm stop-all` gains a `--drop-caches` flag that runs
    `sync; echo 3 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches` under sudo after the
    containers exit, so the kernel releases the page cache that was
    holding the multi-GB GGUF mmaps. VRAM is freed automatically by
    the GPU driver as soon as the containers stop; this only matters
    for system RAM showing as cached.

  Also folded in (originally queued for 0.1.11):
  * `hydra-llm autostart` now accepts the same shortcuts as `start` and
    `stop`: catalog id, GGUF filename, filename without `.gguf`, or the
    numeric `#` from `status`. Previously only the catalog id worked, so
    `autostart 3` errored with `unknown catalog id: 3`.
  * `hydra-llm autostart <id>` now also starts the model immediately
    (in addition to enabling the unit for next login), so the user sees
    the model come up right away. The unit uses `start --no-wait` so
    systemd doesn't tie its lifetime to the model's load time.
  * `loginctl enable-linger` is invoked best-effort on enable, so the
    user unit can come up at boot without an interactive login session.
    No-op on systems without loginctl or where linger is already on.
  * `hydra-llm status` now lists every alias the index numbers refer to,
    not just rows that currently have a container. Previously the `#`
    column showed the alias's position in a hidden union of running
    containers + downloaded catalog entries, so `status` could show
    only `3` while `start 1` resolved to a different model entirely.
    Entries without a container appear with `-` port and `not started`.
  * `start`, `stop`, and `autostart` now echo the resolved alias when
    you pass an index or filename (e.g. `resolved '1' -> dolphin-r1...`),
    so you can ctrl-c if it isn't what you meant.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Thu, 07 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000

hydra-llm (0.1.10-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * `hydra-llm start` now polls the new container's /health endpoint
    and reports one of: `ready in <N>s` (with port for a quick curl),
    `still loading after <N>s` (model still warming up; prints a
    short tail of the container log so you see why), or `container
    exited` (with the last 20 log lines on stderr) when the run
    failed. Pass `--no-wait` to skip the poll, `--wait-timeout` to
    change the 60s deadline. JSON output gains a `health` field.
  * `hydra-llm stop` prints `stopping <alias>...` then `stopped <name>`.
  * `status` and `list` printouts now include a leading `#` column,
    indexed against a stable alphabetical sort over the union of
    `status` rows and downloaded catalog entries. The number is
    accepted by `start`, `stop`, `chat`, and `api` as a shortcut, so
    `hydra-llm stop 1` and `hydra-llm start 1` work. Numeric
    catalog ids still resolve as ids first, only falling back to
    "row index" when no name matches.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hydra-llm (0.1.9-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New `hydra-llm reasoning` subcommand controlling how a model's
    "thinking" / chain-of-thought is exposed. Accepted values:
      none      thinking stays inline in `content` (default, most
                plug-and-play; e.g. `<think>...</think>` blocks).
      deepseek  thinking is split out into a separate
                `reasoning_content` field on each streamed delta and on
                the final message. Clients can render it as a fold-out.
      hide      strip thinking before returning to the client
                (--reasoning-format auto on llama-server).
      off       don't pass the flag; use llama-server's compiled-in
                default (varies by build).
    Bare `reasoning` shows the current value and the accepted set.
    Persists to ~/.config/hydra-llm/config.yaml. Takes effect on
    newly started containers; restart running ones to apply.
  * Default for new installs is `none`, so Gemma's thinking blocks
    are visible in the response by default rather than silently
    stripped.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hydra-llm (0.1.8-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New: model containers now launch with `--predict -1` by default,
    so responses to clients that don't send `max_tokens` are no longer
    silently truncated at llama-server's built-in 128 tokens. The
    model now stops on EOS or when context fills up, which is what
    most users expect. Clients that do send `max_tokens` are
    unaffected; they still win.
  * New `hydra-llm predict` subcommand to change this default.
    Accepted values:
      uncapped    no cap (default)
      off         don't pass --predict; revert to llama-server's 128
      <integer>   positive integer, e.g. 2048
    Run with no args to show the current value and the accepted set.
    Takes effect on newly started containers; restart running ones
    to apply.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Wed, 06 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000

hydra-llm (0.1.7-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix: the `hydrallm` short alias was missing from the actual .deb in
    0.1.5 / 0.1.6. CI builds via `scripts/build-deb.sh` (not via the
    Makefile or `dh_install`), and that script wasn't creating the
    symlink. Added there too. After upgrading, `which hydrallm`
    resolves to /usr/bin/hydrallm and runs the same CLI.

