hydra-llm (0.1.5-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * `hydra-llm start` no longer requires a model id when exactly one
    model is downloaded; it auto-picks that one. With zero downloaded
    it points to `hydra-llm list-online`/`download`; with more than
    one it lists the candidate ids. Explicit `start <id>` is unchanged.
  * New `hydrallm` command, a symlink to `hydra-llm`, for less typing.
    Both names work everywhere; the .deb, user-install, and dev-install
    paths all ship it.
  * Fix: `hydra-llm start` no longer falsely reports "already running"
    when a same-named container is sitting in `Exited` state. The check
    now requires `State == running`; stale exited containers are
    removed and recreated cleanly so the model actually comes back up.

