hydra-llm (0.1.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.
  * Single-binary CLI (hydra-llm) with subcommands: doctor, setup, list,
    list-online, download, remove, start, stop, stop-all, status, api,
    chat, persona, config-path, uninstall, wipe, tray.
  * Two Docker images (vulkan, cpu) built locally on first `setup`. Auto-
    selects vulkan when /dev/dri is present; CPU image is also built as a
    fallback. Transient build errors are retried; persistent failures fall
    back to the CPU image.
  * Curated 11-model catalog of community-quantized GGUFs that download
    anonymously (no Hugging Face token required). Tier filter shows the
    user only models that fit their hardware.
  * Hardware doctor classifies the host into one of: tiny, laptop, halo,
    workstation, server. Strix Halo iGPUs are recognised and marked
    "spill" for models that exceed the VRAM carve-out.
  * Persona files: drop a markdown file with optional YAML front matter
    in ~/.config/hydra-llm/personas/ to make a chat alias.
  * Persistent chat sessions in ~/.local/state/hydra-llm/sessions/.
  * KDE Plasma 6 panel widget (hydra-llm-plasma) with a HAL-eye animated
    indicator, per-model start/stop/chat/logs buttons, live CPU/RAM/GPU/
    VRAM dots, and inline log console.

 -- Ramazan Yavuz <yavuzramazan1994@gmail.com>  Tue, 05 May 2026 16:30:00 +0000
